## Project Overview

This project follows the ML Ops template structure for maintainable and reproducible machine learning projects.

## Project Structure

```
├── configs/          # Hydra configuration files
├── data/
│   ├── processed/   # Processed data
│   └── raw/         # Raw data
├── docs/            # Documentation
├── notebooks/       # Jupyter notebooks
├── reports/         # Generated reports and figures
│   └── figures/
├── src/             # Source code
│   └── {{ repo_name }}/
├── tests/           # Unit tests
└── tasks.py         # Automation tasks
```

## Getting Started

1. Install dependencies:
```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"
```

2. Initialize pre-commit hooks:
```bash
pre-commit install
```

3. Run tests:
```bash
pytest tests/
```

## Development Workflow

The project uses `invoke` for task automation. Main commands:

- `invoke train` - Run training
- `invoke test` - Run tests
- `invoke build-docs` - Build documentation
- `invoke serve-docs` - Serve documentation locally
